@zhreshold I am sorry about that I found I just @ a wrong person. I updated my mxnet code after you modified it, and then I got an error. The following code is where the error happened.

```
#if` (CV_MAJOR_VERSION > 2 || (CV_MAJOR_VERSION == 2 && CV_MINOR_VERSION >=4))
      cv::imdecode(buf, flag, &dst);
    + CHECK(!dst.empty()) << "Decoding failed. Invalid image file.";
```
Here is the error report:
` /home/deeplearning/github/incubator-mxnet/dmlc-core/include/dmlc/./logging.h:308: [11:13:06] src/io/image_io.cc:160: Check failed: !dst.empty() Decoding failed. Invalid image file.`
What should I do to correct this error?

@solin319 thanks for bringing these up in this issue.
@ZiyueHuang  `wait_to_write` does what it says - it waits until you can write to this NDArray. `send_buf.WaitToWrite` ensures `push` won't start until the previous `pull` has completed. But in retrospect, it hurts performance significantly. Normally in a neural net, we don't need such ordering guarantee during training explicitly. We only need to ensure `pull` happens after the `push`. 

After discussing with @mli I'm going to remove this `WaitToWrite` and update the document that people are aware there's no guarantee that push always happens after the previous pull. 

